label50.Text
data.value:
The level to which (from black=0) colors are still interpreted as background ( black). Anything beyond that is interpreted as text. When gaps in the letters and numbers *) you should put down the level a bit. If numbers or letters are connected by bridges pixels *) , the level should be set slightly higher.
*) see the graphics in "Filter-Test"

data.name: label52.Text
data.value: In order to reduce the recognition time you can set a threshold quantity. The areas on which less dark pixels (= text) to see are as specified in the threshold will be completely ignored in the recognition. The threshold value should be greater than the number of pixels of a "-" be but also smaller than number of pixel number of a "1" (because this is the digit with the fewest number of pixels in it). So all "-" and less are ignored , all "1" and other digits are detected.
